@startuml SD-09_AI_Chat

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName "Arial"
skinparam defaultFontSize 17
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 300

skinparam participant {
    BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
    BorderColor #555555
    BorderThickness 1
    FontColor #000000
    FontStyle plain
}
skinparam actor {
    BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
    BorderColor #555555
    BorderThickness 1
    FontColor #000000
}
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #333333
    ArrowThickness 1
    ArrowFontColor #000000
    ArrowFontSize 16
    LifeLineBorderColor #333333
    LifeLineBorderThickness 1
    LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
    GroupBodyBackgroundColor #F8F8F8
    GroupBorderColor #888888
    GroupBorderThickness 1
    GroupHeaderFontColor #000000
    DividerBackgroundColor #E8E8E8
    DividerFontColor #000000
    DividerBorderColor #AAAAAA
    DividerBorderThickness 1
    ParticipantBorderThickness 1
}
skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
    BorderColor #999999
    BorderThickness 1
    FontColor #000000
}

actor       "User"         as User
participant "Web\nUI"      as UI
participant "AI Chat\nBackend" as Back
participant "Gemini\nAPI"  as Gemini
database    "DB"           as DB

== Chat Interaction ==

User -> UI   : Click chat button\n(auto-hides on scroll)
UI   -> UI   : Open panel\nShow suggestions
User -> UI   : Type message,\nClick "Send"
UI   -> UI   : Append to local state\n{ role:"user", content }
UI   -> Back : POST /api/ai/chat\n{ message, history[], scanId? }

alt scanId provided
    Back -> DB  : findOne(Scan + Asset +\nFindings + AIAnalysis)
    DB --> Back : scan context
end

Back  -> DB   : count(Assets, Scans,\ncritical/high Findings)
DB  --> Back  : org stats

Back  -> Back : Build prompt:\n"TRACE AI + CONTEXT"
Back  -> Gemini : startChat().sendMessage()\n[gemini-2.0-flash, temp:0.7]
Gemini --> Back : response.text()

Back --> UI  : 200 OK { reply }
UI  --> User : Display AI reply

note right of UI
  Chat history maintained
  client-side and sent
  with each message
end note

@enduml
